<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07946</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING RESTAURANTS AND OTHER SIMILAR FOOD ESTABLISHMENTS TO DISCLOSE AND DISPLAY NUTRITIONAL INFORMATION OF FOOD AND BEVERAGES ON THEIR MENUS AND MENU BOARDS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to help Filipinos make an informed and healthier decision on their food choices by providing that food establishments disclose the corresponding nutrient content, in a clear and conspicuous manner as regard to:  total calories; calories from fat; total fat; saturated fat; trans fat; cholesterol; Sodium; total carbohydrates; dietary fiber; sugars; and protein
Provides that the statement:  “2,000 calories a day is used for general nutrition advice, but calorie needs vary” be posted prominently to enable consumers to understand, in the context of a total daily diet, the significance of calorie information.
Also includes provision for menus and menu boards targeting children with options as a substitute for or in addition to the above statement.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Menu Labeling Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SUANSING, ESTRELLITA B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-24</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-08-08)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2018-08-01</td></tr></table>